<body>

    <div class="infographic-container">
        <header>
            <h1>Who is a Public Sector Customer?</h1>
            <p>A clear definition across three primary categories.</p>
        </header>

        <main class="card-container">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-icon">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-landmark-dome"></i>
                </div>
                <h2>Government Entity</h2>
                <p class="definition">
                    Any national, state, provincial, municipal, local, First Nations, or Native American governmental organization.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Includes any department, agency, ministry, instrumentality, or branch of government.</li>
                    <li>Also includes public international organizations like the IMF, United Nations, and the World Bank.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-icon">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-building-user"></i>
                </div>
                <h2>Government Owned Entity</h2>
                <p class="definition">
                    Organizations that are owned or controlled by a Government Entity, also known as State-Owned Enterprises (SOEs).
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Companies with 30% or more government ownership, control, or funding.</li>
                    <li>Entities performing government functions (e.g., public schools, public hospitals, state-owned oil companies, utilities).</li>
                    <li>Companies owned or controlled by a royal family or (outside the U.S.) a political party.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-icon">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-user-tie"></i>
                </div>
                <h2>Government Personnel</h2>
                <p class="definition">
                    Individuals who are employed by, or act on behalf of, a government or government-owned entity.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Employees at any level of government (national, regional, local).</li>
                    <li>Political appointees, elected officials, and candidates for political office.</li>
                    <li>Members of a royal family.</li>
                    <li>All employees of Government Entities and Government-owned Entities.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </main>
    </div>

